      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "RETOPOLGY SMOOTH — A/B against the OFF baseline.\n\nTwo AtlasExportReliefMesh nodes share ONE solve + image:\n· left = retopo_method OFF  (the default; torn silhouette, DMP-correct)\n· right = retopo_method SMOOTH (trimesh Taubin relax, 12 iterations)\n\nSMOOTH is topology-PRESERVING — same faces, same vertex count — so the\n1:1 vertex-UV mapping baked in build_relief_mesh stays valid and UVs are\nNOT regenerated (pure numpy, trimesh is already a dep — runs everywhere,\nno extra install). It only moves vertex positions: relaxes the noisy mono-\ndepth ripple into a smoother surface for a cleaner DCC import.\n\nExport-only doctrine: retopology NEVER touches the live viewport projection\nmesh or solve.proxy_geometry — it runs once on the resolved ReliefMesh,\nafter any hole-fill, before the OBJ/GLB writers.\n\nCompare the two OBJs in Maya/ZBrush/Blender: same vert/face count, smoother\nsurface on the right, identical UVs/textures."
      ],
      "title": "Note"
    }
